

---

Dependencies

System Packages (Ubuntu/Debian)

Install required system packages:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y \
  python3 \
  python3-venv \
  python3-pip \
  git \
  curl \
  jq \
  lm-sensors \
  ethtool

---

Python Environment

Create and activate a virtual environment:

python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

Install Python dependencies:

pip install \
  python-telegram-bot \
  requests


---

Ollama (Local LLM Runtime)

Install Ollama:

curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

Start the service:

ollama serve

Pull models:

ollama pull llama3
ollama pull llama3.1:8b
ollama pull qwen2.5:7b
ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:7b


---

Web UI (Optional)

Run Open WebUI using Docker:

docker run -d \
  -p 3000:8080 \
  -e OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://<SERVER_IP>:11434 \
  --name open-webui \
  ghcr.io/open-webui/open-webui:main


---

VPN (Remote Access)

Install and start Tailscale:

curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh
sudo tailscale up


---

Telegram Bot Configuration

Create a bot using BotFather and configure environment variables:

TELEGRAM_TOKEN=your_token_here
OLLAMA_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/chat
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5:7b
ALLOWED_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id

Store these values in a .env file in the project directory.


---

Systemd Service

Example service file:

[Unit]
Description=Telegram Ollama Bot
After=network.target

[Service]
User=kraken
WorkingDirectory=/data/projects/telegram-bot
ExecStart=/data/projects/telegram-bot/.venv/bin/python bot.py
Restart=always
EnvironmentFile=/data/projects/telegram-bot/.env

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

